text.section:
The Authority may:
adopt bylaws for the conduct of its business;
adopt a seal;
maintain an office at a place it designates;
maintain facilities for the purpose of holding hearings under this subtitle;
employ a staff;
accept a grant, a loan, or any other assistance in any form from any public or private source, subject to the provisions of this subtitle;
enter into contracts and execute the instruments necessary or convenient to carry out this subtitle to accomplish its purposes; and
do all things necessary or convenient to carry out the powers expressly granted by this subtitle.
